<h2 id="more">Forest Lawn</h2>
<p>A former town located in the south-east quadrant of Calgary, Forest Lawn is now a flourishing and one of the most desirable residential communities in the city. The neighborhood is surrounded by 48 Street SE on the east, 8 Avenue SE on the north and the 36 Street SE on the west and the 26 Avenue SE on the south.</p>
<h2>Forest Lawn Real Estate</h2>
<p>Originally incorporated as the Town of the Forest Lawn, the community in Forest Lawn still retains its archaic charm in its architectural styles and landscape. A typical suburb of Calgary, Forest Lawn Real Estate is a historic neighborhood that offers a variety of housing options from townhomes to apartment condos that are regularly listed at an average price of $330,000. Given the fact that most of the residential properties date back nearly a century ago, the homes for sale in Forest lawns have undergone a series of renovations to keep them in sync with the changing demands of the contemporary homebuyer.</p>
<div id="pics">#fc-forest-lawn#</div>
<h2>Forest Lawn and International Avenue</h2>
<p>International Avenue is a vibrant and ethnically diverse culture and business hub situated on 17 Avenue SE in southeast Calgary. Known as the &lsquo;mini United Nation&rsquo; of Calgary, the area is home to an eclectic mix of retail businesses from across the world, featuring some of the best of the world&rsquo;s cuisines, services, industries and auto businesses. Spanning 35 blocks on 17 Avenue SE, International Avenue takes its visitors &lsquo;around the world&rsquo; to enjoy a stunning mix of sounds, sights, foods and experiences.</p>
<p>The Avenue is part of Forest Lawn, which is a former town and neighbourhood located in the southeast quadrant of Calgary in Alberta. The southern border of the neighbourhood is flanked by 26 Avenue SE while the western border is marked by 36 Street SE. The northern border is marked by 8 Avenue SE while parts of 48 Street SE and 52 Street SE occupy the eastern border.</p>
<p>Forest Lawn also encompasses, apart from the current Forest Lawn neighbourhood, some portions of Albert Park or Radisson Heights and Southview that are located in the western part of the neighbourhood and parts of Forest Lawn Industrial and Penbrooke Meadows to the east.</p>
<p>17 Avenue SE bisects the neighbourhood of Forest Lawn and is part of the Business Revitalization Zone.</p>
